description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a band 6 Specialist nurses to support children with neurodevelopmental conditions such as ASD (Autistic Spectrum Disorder/condition) and ADHD (Attention Deficit Hyperactivity disorder).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neurodevelopmental team is made up of paediatricians, nurses, health care assistants and admin who support children through a pathway of investigations, diagnosis and care planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is open to all registered nurses with transferrable skills or experience of working with children and young people with ADHD and or ASD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide comprehensive assessments, reports and contribute to case discussion and care planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent assessment, risk management, organisational and communication skills are essential along with the ability to use your initiative, manage your time effectively and work as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are planned to take place on 20th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pippa White - Head of Servcie&lt;/p&gt;
